 binary system with a\nheavy WD companion, PSR J1755-25 has a significant orbital eccentricity of\n0.09, and PSR J1759-24 is likely to be a long-orbit eclipsing binary with\norbital period of the order of tens of years. Comparison of our\nnewly-discovered pulsar sample to the known population suggests that they\nbelong to an older population. Furthermore, we demonstrate that our current\npulsar detection yield is as expected from population synthesis.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 29 Apr 2015 20:01:31 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-05-01"}
